name: Lodash
contents: A modern JavaScript utility library delivering modularity, performance, & extras. Lodash is released under the MIT license & supports modern environments.

name: Redux-Thunk
contents: Redux Thunk middleware allows you to write action creators that return a function instead of an action. The thunk can be used to delay the dispatch of an action, or to dispatch only if a certain condition is met.

name: ESLint
contents: ESLint is an open source JavaScript linting utility originally created by Nicholas C. Zakas in June 2013. Code linting is a type of static analysis that is frequently used to find problematic patterns or code that doesn't adhere to certain style guidelines.

name: Babel
contents: Babel has support for the latest version of JavaScript through syntax transformers. These plugins allow you to use new syntax, right now without waiting for browser support.

name: Axios
contents: Promise based HTTP client for the browser and node.js. With Axios, you can make XMLHttpRequests from the browser or Node with the full Promise Api.
